76561197972107045,Recommended,246300,9972329,"Posted: 29 April, 2014",all,Sarge4id,"Paranormal - One of the greatest edge-of-your-seat horror games I have played. It's up there with Outlast. Paranormal takes on the elements and features (sounds, effects, visuals) as the Paranormal movie trilogy. It's your Blair Witch Project type of set up - found footage, you know the type. The plot is simple, you document paranormal activity in a house and try avoid being killed by enviromental and accidental mistakes. For isntance: You have to sleep to recharge your camera's battery. If you run out of juice before you get to bed, you will probably end up dead. The game also uses sound efx to set a scary atmosphere. Footsteps, doors closing, items breaking, shouting, crying, etc. Plus we cant leave out the roaring sound when something ""paranormal"" is about to happen. As for replayability, each experience is different. Objects are located in different places, things happen in some play throughs and don't in others. Over all, if your looking for a good scary game like slenderman or outlast, this is a good game to add to your horror game collection."
